    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of sheep of many breeds, descended from the wild mouflon of Europe and Asia. Sheep were among the earliest animals to be domesticated. They are raised for fleece, meat, and milk.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
